---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy | Stitch & Spec">
  <article class="policy-page">
    <header class="page-hero compact">
      <p class="publication-kicker">Publication standards</p>
      <h1>Editorial policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">This site is built as a citation-ready research tool, not a hype-driven affiliate blog.</p>
    </header>
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>How the research is held accountable</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Every research page starts with a direct bottom-line answer.</li>
        <li>Claims should point to manufacturer documentation, retailer specifications, manuals, or clearly labeled expert sources.</li>
        <li>Comparison tables use neutral criteria: project fit, machine limits, serviceability, and upgrade risk.</li>
        <li>Affiliate links are stored in a data layer so merchant swaps do not rewrite editorial conclusions.</li>
        <li>Pages carry visible last-updated dates and reader-facing FAQ sections.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
